        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sil­ver Lin­ings</p>
    <p>This com­prises two dig­i­tal projects fea­tur­ing mu­sic, visual arts and sto­ry­telling. In Strings Of Dreams, SMU (Sin­ga­pore Man­age­ment Univer­sity) Guitaris­simo presents three Ni­i­bori gui­tar pieces, vi­su­alised by award-win­ning dig­i­tal artist Race Kre­hel. Each piece cap­tures a dif­fer­ent phase ex­pe­ri­enced by peo­ple around the world dur­ing Covid-19. The Dream Keeper is a first-time col­lab­o­ra­tion be­tween SMU Cham­ber Choir and SMU Art­dicted. As the choir sings, draw­ings by SMU Art­dicted light up pro­gres­sively on a dig­i­tal night sky, each rep­re­sent­ing the hope and loss felt dur­ing the pan­demic. Part of A-Part, SMU’s Arts Fes­ti­val 2020. WHEN: Till Oct 30 AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: smu.sg/arts­fest</p>


